# Git Ignore Rules

## Critical Files That MUST Be Gitignored

These files should NEVER be committed to version control:

### Environment & Secrets

```gitignore
# ALWAYS ignore - contains secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.staging
.env.production
.env.test

# Credential files
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
credentials.json
service-account*.json
```

### Credential Documentation

```gitignore
# NEVER commit files with passwords/secrets in names
*CREDENTIAL*.md
*PASSWORD*.md
*SECRET*.md
SECURE_*.md
*_CREDENTIALS.md
LOGIN_INFO*.md
API_KEYS*.md
```

### Database Files

```gitignore
# Database dumps - can contain sensitive data
backups/
*.sql
*.sql.gz
*.sql.zip
*.dump
*.rdb

# SQLite files
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
```

## Files to KEEP in Repository

These files should be committed (they're templates without secrets):

```gitignore
# Keep these - they're templates
!.env.example
!env.example
!env.*.example
!*.template
!deploy/env.production.example
```

## Common Patterns by Category

### Build Outputs

```gitignore
build/
dist/
.cache/
.next/
out/
.remix/
```

### Dependencies

```gitignore
node_modules/
.pnp/
```

### Testing

```gitignore
coverage/
.nyc_output/
test-results/
playwright-report/
```

### Docker

```gitignore
# Image archives (large files)
*.tar
docker-images/
*.image.tar.gz

# Local volume data
postgres_data/
redis_data/
```

### IDE & OS

```gitignore
.vscode/
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```

## When Creating New Projects

Always verify the `.gitignore` includes:

1. All `.env` variants
2. Database backup files
3. Credential documentation files
4. Build outputs
5. Node modules
6. IDE files
7. OS files

## Verification Command

Run this to check for accidentally committed secrets:

```bash
# Check for common secret patterns
git log --all -p | grep -i "api_key\|api-key\|apikey\|secret\|password\|token" | head -20
```

## Before Each Commit

Verify sensitive files are not staged:

```bash
# Check staged files
git status

# Verify no .env files
git diff --cached --name-only | grep -E "\.env" && echo "WARNING: .env file staged!"
```
